 <sect1 xml:id="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_ga_maint1">
  <title>February 2015 (Documentation Maintenance Update)</title>

  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.timezone" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      With NTP disabled it is recommended to avoid writing system time to
      the hardware clock. Thus set <literal>SYSTOHC=no</literal>.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Adjustments for <xref linkend="cha.smt"/> because of the switch from
        &ncc; to &scc;
        (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=857639"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        <xref linkend="sec.y2.userman.adv.passw"/>: Password Settings,
        Expiration Date is expiring user accounts in YAST Users module
        (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=743874"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Various bugfixes for <xref linkend="cha.update.sle"/>:
       </para>
       <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
        <listitem>
         <para>
          The named upgrade path does not work - There is no working upgrade
          path from SLES 11 SP3 to SLES 12 on Linux for System z
          (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=907648"/>).
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          [doc] 7.5 The Atomic Update
          (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=905330"/>).
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          [doc] 7.5 Upgrading to SLE 12
          (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=904188"/>).
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          [doc] 7.4 Intermediate step: Updating SLE 11 SP2 to SLE 11 SP3
          (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=904186"/>).
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          [doc] 7.2 Supported Upgrade Paths to SLE
          (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=904182"/>).
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          [doc] Potentially misleading info around the 6 months overlap
          support
          (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=902463"/>).
         </para>
        </listitem>
       </itemizedlist>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
 <sect1 xml:id="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_ga">
  <title>October 2014 (Initial Release of &productname; 12)</title>

  <variablelist>
<!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->
   <xi:include href="common_docupdates_general_i.xml" parse="xml"/>
<!-- 2. Installation on AMD64 and Intel 64 -->
   <varlistentry os="sles">
    <term><xref linkend="cha.x86"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated system requirements.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- 3. Installation on IBM POWER  -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.power"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added POWER8 to the list of supported hardware (Fate#315272).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        &sls; 12 for POWER has moved to Little Endian. Updated affected
        parts of the documentation.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- 4. Installation on IBM System z -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.zseries"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the list of supported platforms: Removed IBM Series z9 and
        z10 machines and added IBM zEnterprise BC12.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the memory and disk space requirements.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed instructions on how to IPL from tape&mdash;this is no
        longer supported.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Rewrote large parts of <xref linkend="sec.prep.netcfg"/> to remove
        redundant information and make it more concise.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed references to Token Ring, which is no longer supported
        (Fate#313154).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 6. Installation with YaST -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.inst"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Completely rewrote the chapter because of the new installation
        workflow.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The installation routine now supports setting up multiple network
        devices during the installation (Fate#315680):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.network"/>
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The installation proposal contains a separate
        <filename>/home</filename> partition formatted with XFS (Fate#316637
        and Fate#316624):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.partitioning"/>
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed occurrences of the &yast; Repair module which has been
        dropped (Fate#308670).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Update repositories are added after having registered with &scc;
        and can be used during installation (Fate#312012):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.addon"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Extensions and modules can be added to the system during the
        installation (Fate#316548):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.conf.manual.cc"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        &sled; can be installed as an add-on on top of &sls;
        (Fate#316436): <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.addon"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        The HW crypto stack for IBM &zseries; can be selected for
        installation via a pattern (Fate#316143):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.proposal.sofware"/>
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Automatically importing SSH keys from a previous installation can be
        disabled (Fate#314982):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast.start.parameters.keys_users"/>
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 7. Updating SUSE Linux Enterprise -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.update.sle"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added new section: <xref linkend="sec.update.sle12"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 8. Setting Up Hardware Components with YaST -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.y2.hw"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed the following sections as the respective &yast; modules
        are no longer included: <citetitle>Hardware Information</citetitle>,
        <citetitle>Setting Up Graphics Card and Monitor</citetitle>,
        <citetitle>Mouse Model</citetitle>, and <citetitle>Setting Up a
        Scanner</citetitle>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed content about mouse setup and adjusted
        <xref linkend="cha.y2.hw.keym"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 9. Installing or Removing Software -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.y2.sw"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Completely rewrote <xref linkend="sec.updater"/> because of changes
        in the GNOME software updater.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 10. Installing Add-On Products  -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.add-ons"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Installing add-on products or software extensions is now also
        possible without access to physical media. Added the following new
        sections: <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.register"/> and
        <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.extensions"/>. Modified
        <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.install"/> accordingly.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 16. Subscription Management -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.smt"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        For registering clients against an &smt; server,
        <command>suse_register</command> has been replaced with
        <command>SUSEConnect</command> (Fate#316585).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated chapter <xref linkend="cha.addon_creator"/> according to
        <link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=861855"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated chapter <xref linkend="cha.productcreator"/> and added
        chapter <xref linkend="cha.imgcreator"/> according to
        <link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=864033"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated section <xref linkend="sec.updater"/> according to
        <link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=839692"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed section <citetitle>Using Fingerprint
        Authentication</citetitle>. Further minor corrections and additions
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=857680"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed obsolete parameter <literal>OsaMedium</literal> from
        parmfile and Cobbler examples
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=860404"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Additions in section <xref linkend="sec.fb.customize"/>
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=861866"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added instructions on how to add secondary languages during
        installation
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=870482"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!--Installing Multiple Kernel Versions -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.tuning.multikernel"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Multiversion feature (more than one kernel installed) is enabled by
        default
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=891805"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Warn about incompatible Kernel Module Packages (KPMs)
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=891805"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
